#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Kosala "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Issattasutta → issatthasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Issattasutta "
msgstr "24. Archery "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.99, pts2ed1.220, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.3"
msgid "“kattha nu kho, bhante, dānaṃ dātabban”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, where should a gift be given?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.4"
msgid "“Yattha kho, mahārāja, cittaṃ pasīdatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Wherever your heart feels inspired, great king.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.5"
msgid "“Kattha pana, bhante, dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, where is a gift very fruitful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.6"
msgid "“Aññaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, kattha dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, aññaṃ panetaṃ kattha dinnaṃ mahapphalanti? "
msgstr "“Where a gift should be given is one thing, great king, but where a gift is very fruitful is another. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.7"
msgid "Sīlavato kho, mahārāja, dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, no tathā dussīle. "
msgstr "A gift is very fruitful when it’s given to an ethical person, not so much to an unethical person. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.8"
msgid "Tena hi, mahārāja, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā, te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi. "
msgstr "Well then, great king, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "What do you think, great king? "

#. VAR: samupabyūḷho → samūpabbūḷho (bj, pts2) | samupabbuḷho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.10"
msgid "idha tyassa yuddhaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ saṅgāmo samupabyūḷho. "
msgstr "Suppose you were at war, ready to fight a battle. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.11"
msgid "Atha āgaccheyya khattiyakumāro asikkhito akatahattho akatayoggo akatūpāsano bhīru chambhī utrāsī palāyī. "
msgstr "Then along comes an aristocrat youth who is untrained, inexpert, unfit, inexperienced. And he’s fearful, cowardly, trembling, quick to flee. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.12"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti? "
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.13"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, bhareyyaṃ taṃ purisaṃ, na ca me attho tādisena purisenā”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sir, I would have no use for such a man.” "

# NOTE: Note that, while the khattiyas were often said to be the warrior class, there is no difference here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.14"
msgid "“Atha āgaccheyya brāhmaṇakumāro asikkhito … pe … "
msgstr "“What about a brahmin youth, "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.15"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya vessakumāro asikkhito … pe … "
msgstr "a merchant youth, "

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.16"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya suddakumāro asikkhito … pe … "
msgstr "or a worker youth who was similar?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.17"
msgid "na ca me attho tādisena purisenā”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sir, I would have no use for such a man.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.222, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.24:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "“What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.2"
msgid "idha tyassa yuddhaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ saṅgāmo samupabyūḷho. "
msgstr "Suppose you were at war, ready to fight a battle. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.3"
msgid "Atha āgaccheyya khattiyakumāro susikkhito katahattho katayoggo katūpāsano abhīru acchambhī anutrāsī apalāyī. "
msgstr "Then along comes an aristocrat youth who is trained, expert, fit, experienced. And he’s fearless, brave, bold, standing his ground. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.4"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti? "
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:2.5"
msgid "“Bhareyyāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca me tādisena purisenā”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir, I would have a use for such a man.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:2.6"
msgid "“Atha āgaccheyya brāhmaṇakumāro … pe … "
msgstr "“What about a brahmin youth, "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.7"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya vessakumāro … pe … "
msgstr "a merchant youth, "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.8"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya suddakumāro susikkhito katahattho katayoggo katūpāsano abhīru acchambhī anutrāsī apalāyī. "
msgstr "or a worker youth who was similar? "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.9"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti? "
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:2.10"
msgid "“Bhareyyāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca me tādisena purisenā”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir, I would have a use for such a man.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.100, pts2ed1.223, sc3
#. VAR: yasmā kasmā cepi → yasmā cepi (si, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, mahārāja, yasmā kasmā cepi kulā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca hoti pañcaṅgavippahīno pañcaṅgasamannāgato, tasmiṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "“In the same way, a gift to anyone who has given up five factors and possesses five factors is very fruitful, no matter what family they’ve gone forth from. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti? "
msgstr "What are the five factors they’ve given up? "

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.3"
msgid "Kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā hoti. "
msgstr "Sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.4"
msgid "Imāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti. "
msgstr "These are the five factors they’ve given up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.5"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato hoti? "
msgstr "What are the five factors they possess? "

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.6"
msgid "Asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "The entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.7"
msgid "Imehi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "These are the five factors they possess. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.8"
msgid "Iti pañcaṅgavippahīne pañcaṅgasamannāgate dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti. "
msgstr "I say that a gift to anyone who has given up these five factors and possesses these five factors is very fruitful.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.10"
msgid "satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: Issattaṃ → issatthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
#. VAR: balavīriyañca → balaviriyañca (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.1"
msgid "“Issattaṃ balavīriyañca, "
msgstr "“Any youth skilled at archery, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ vijjetha māṇave; "
msgstr "powerful and vigorous, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ yuddhattho bhare rājā, "
msgstr "would be employed by a king going to war—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.4"
msgid "nāsūraṃ jātipaccayā. "
msgstr "one is not a coward because of one’s birth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.1"
msgid "Tatheva khantisoraccaṃ, "
msgstr "Just so, whoever is settled "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.2"
msgid "dhammā yasmiṃ patiṭṭhitā; "
msgstr "in the qualities of patience and gentleness, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.3"
msgid "Ariyavuttiṃ medhāviṃ, "
msgstr "a clever person with noble conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.4"
msgid "hīnajaccampi pūjaye. "
msgstr "should be venerated even if they’re low born. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.1"
msgid "Kāraye assame ramme, "
msgstr "You should build lovely hermitages "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.2"
msgid "vāsayettha bahussute; "
msgstr "and settle learned people in them. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.3"
msgid "Papañca vivane kayirā, "
msgstr "You should set up water supplies in barren regions "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.4"
msgid "dugge saṅkamanāni ca. "
msgstr "and passages in places hard to travel. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.224, sc7
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.1"
msgid "Annaṃ pānaṃ khādanīyaṃ, "
msgstr "Food, drink, edibles, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.2"
msgid "vatthasenāsanāni ca; "
msgstr "clothes, and lodgings "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.3"
msgid "Dadeyya ujubhūtesu, "
msgstr "should be given to the upright ones, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.4"
msgid "vippasannena cetasā. "
msgstr "with a clear and confident heart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.1"
msgid "Yathā hi megho thanayaṃ, "
msgstr "The thundering rain cloud, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.2"
msgid "vijjumālī satakkaku; "
msgstr "its hundred peaks wreathed in lightning, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.3"
msgid "Thalaṃ ninnañca pūreti, "
msgstr "pours down over the rich earth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.4"
msgid "abhivassaṃ vasundharaṃ. "
msgstr "soaking the uplands and valleys. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.1"
msgid "Tatheva saddho sutavā, "
msgstr "So too an astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.2"
msgid "abhisaṅkhacca bhojanaṃ; "
msgstr "faithful and learned, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.3"
msgid "Vanibbake tappayati, "
msgstr "should prepare a meal to satisfy "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.4"
msgid "annapānena paṇḍito. "
msgstr "renunciates with food and drink. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.1"
msgid "Āmodamāno pakireti, "
msgstr "Rejoicing, they distribute, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.2"
msgid "detha dethāti bhāsati; "
msgstr "saying, ‘Give! give!’ "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.3"
msgid "Taṃ hissa gajjitaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "For that is their thunder, "

# NOTE: The Upanishads say that the thunder is the roar of Brahma. Thus it seems that, while the animist heritage of deva=sky is usually backgrounded, here it is rather more specific.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.4"
msgid "devasseva pavassato; "
msgstr "like the gods when it rains. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.5"
msgid "Sā puññadhārā vipulā, "
msgstr "That stream of merit so abundant "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.6"
msgid "dātāraṃ abhivassatī”ti. "
msgstr "showers down on the giver.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
